page.title: 09ECOLOGY
page.content: RESIDENT BIRDS Heron and Mallard are seen infrequently.Raptors include Buzzard,Sparrowhawk and Kestrel.Red legged partridge and Pheasant are common,but Grey Partridge much less so.Of waders, Lapwing abound,but Snipe,Woodcock and Curlew nest in small numbers.Moorhens are occasional, and Black headed,Herring and Lesser Black backed Gulls on passage.Wood pigeons abound,Stock Doves and Collared Doves less so.Barn Owl and Little Owl have been seen, but Tawny Owl is only common Owl.Kingfisher is very rare,as is Lesser Spotted Woodpecker,with Great Spotted frequent and Green occasional.Many Skylarks and corvids represented are Raven,Carrion Crow,Rook,Jackdaw,Magpie and Jay.Great,Blue,Coal,Willow and Long tailed Tits are common.Marsh Tit rare.
